               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; groups of lines alternating with black lines in the incipit page of Text I-1; headings and incipits of the texts, their sections and subsections; titles of the Biblical books and other works; names of Hebrew letters in Text I-8; directives for the ministers; abbreviations in Texts I-8 and I-9; elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic numerals or their elements.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>The correct sequence of the quires, between quires V and XII, should be: V-VII-VI-VIII-IX-XI-X-XII.</note>
                     <note>For Text I-5, the correct sequence of the quires should be: V-VII-VI; for Text I-6, the correct sequence should be: VI-VIII; for Text I-7, the correct sequencer should be: IX-XI-X-XII.</note>
                     <note>- On fol. 149ra, the incipit of the "Mäṣḥafä dorho" (in Text I-9) is as follows:</note>
                     <note>ድርሳን፡ ትምህረተ[sic]፡ ዘአበዊነ፡ ሐዋርያት። ቅዱሳን፡ ዘመሐሩነ፡ መንፈሳዊን፡ እሉ፡ እሙንቱ፡ እለ፡…</note>
                     <note>On fol. 158rb, "Mäṣḥafä dorho" ends with a subscriptio on the translation of the text from Arabic into Gǝʿǝz, during the time of King Yoḥannǝs (probably Yoḥannǝs IV, r. 1872-89); the note reads:</note>
                     <note>ወተተርጉመት፡ ዛቲ: መጽሐፍ፡ እምዐረቢ፡ ለግእዝ፡ በዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡ እንዘ፡ ንጉሥነ። ዮሐንስ።</note>
                     <note>It seems that the original date of the translation according to the “year of mercy” has been dropped; the indication to King Yoḥannǝs may refer not to the translation date but to the time when the the Ms. was produced.</note>
                     <note>- On fol. 168vb, the text ends with a short concluding praise to God, in Amharic:</note>
                     <note>ተመስገን፡ ጌታዬ፡ ቸሩ፡ አምላክ፡ በሰላም፡ በጤና፡ ይሕነን፡ ነን[sic]መጽሐፍ፡ ያስፈጸምኸኝ። ። ። ። ። ።</note>
                  </msItem>
